D) the idea of FCFS on atleast naggy/vox is scary to me. they are dragons that need a specific lvl of people to take..and for people to get pick up groups for them....will make taking them down much harder. And i think the point should be making sure they die as fast as possible. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uphazy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Phazy</A> at: 4/23/01 8:39:56 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uadunofbrell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Adun of Brell</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Burn the Witch! [Mod]</span><br>  Posts: 1767<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/23/01 9:15:29 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.pangea.ca/~grinch/ladun.jpg width=67 height=150></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What does the future hold: Nagafen/Vox</span><hr size=1> Here are the problems I see with Nagafen &amp; Vox.<br>
<br>
1.) Because of the extended rotation, &amp; the level cap, Nag/Vox raiders are often higher than 52 by the time their turn comes around.  This leads to people signing up for the dragons before they're ready &amp; actually extending the list, aggravating the problem.<br>
<br>
2.) Because more experienced raiders leave Nag/Vox behind when they hit 52, many guilds that CAN raid Nag/Vox lack the leadership &amp; experience to lead a successful raid.<br>
<br>
3.) Any guild that has active players will have a difficulty maintaining a L47-52 player base.  To kill the dragons, you need a variety of classes.  Guilds have a VERY difficult time providing any significant portion of the people needed.<br>
<br>
A significant portion of the names on Nag &amp; Vox are invalid.  They're people that signed up just to get their shot.  Their capability of leading a successful raid is marginal, and heavily depends on signups.<br>
<br>
In several cases, the guild has their name on the list so they can &quot;claim&quot; a drop off the dragon.<br>
<br>
That is why things must change.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> My proposal for the old world dragons.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
My vision for Nagafen &amp; Vox is a place where people of the appropriate level can sign up NOW to do the dragons NOW.  Not six months down the road, but at the present time.  It's a place where the people with the experience &amp; knowledge to kill the dragons can meet with the various people that will help them make it happen.  It's not based on guild tag, but on cooperation.  It will involve everyone that's interested in dropping the dragons, &amp; is of the appropriate level.<br>
<br>
I want to see things like they were when Nag/Vox first fell on Brell.  Where all people interested &amp; of the appropriate level got together &amp; made it happen.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Changes:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
1.) The rotation will be removed.  Too many guilds/Indy's on the list are no longer valid for a Nag/Vox killing.  They lack the resources in guild to pull it off.  Very few guilds (If any at all) have even HALF the people required (47-52) to make for a successful Nagafen/Vox raid.  This means that people are on the list for selfish &amp; exclusive reasons.  They want to claim loot, or they want to take only their select group, excluding others.<br>
<br>
2.)  In it's place, a forum be created.  In this forum, the leaders with the experience to kill Nag/Vox can coordinate with the people that can &amp; want to kill them.  In this forum, the leaders can post that they will be taking a raid to kill the dragons.  If multiple leaders are interested at the same time, they can pool their forces together.  The emphasis is on cooperation, and server effort, not on individual guilds.  The raids belong to the server, not any guild.<br>
<br>
3.)  Loot claiming will not be permitted.  Raids will be run for the good of the server, and to give people the experience of killing a dragon.<br>
<br>
4.) An ever changing &quot;Dragon killing community&quot; will be formed.  As people level past 52, they will leave the community.  As people come into the 47-52 range, they will enter the community.<br>
<br>
The goal is to pool resources as a server, for the good of the server.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Advantages</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
*People can participate in an open dragon raid, without skewed loot rolls.<br>
*The leaders can coordinate with the people who can help them kill dragons.<br>
*Raiders can obtain the information they need on gear, resist, tactics from experienced leaders, to lead SUCCESSFUL raids.<br>
*Vox WILL drop consistently, because the experience, and the people can get together &amp; have good raids.  The white scale will become far less of an issue for raids.<br>
*People won't need to STAY 52 to raid a dragon, because the chance will ALWAYS be there.  People will no longer have to wait for &quot;Their guild&quot; to get a shot at a dragon.<br>
<br>
I feel this type of system is much more in the &quot;Spirit of Brell&quot;.  It's one of cooperation, and mutual support.<br>
<br>
I will actively support this system by de-levelling Adun down to 52, &amp; helping to lead raids on Nagafen &amp; Vox.  I feel that actively supporting this, &amp; showing that it can work is the best way of bringing in a new era of cooperation on a server wide basis on Brell.  Because of the server side filtering changes, dragon raids CAN take too many people, &amp; not be doomed.  It's no longer critical that un-needed classes be excluded for reasons of lag.  There is space to include many.<br>
<br>
After a raid, the raid leaders will post about the raid, about who won what items, and any problems they encountered.  This way, the community can celebrate with the people that have won very special items.  Future raids can learn from the problems that the raid came accross.  The raid's makeup is apparent, so future raids can respectfully request that people not &quot;hog&quot; the raids.  I KNOW that we can share resources like the dragons without an extensive, out of date list that doesn't truly represent the L47-52 population anymore.<br>
<br>
I volunteer to serve as a moderator in the forum, along with 2 or 3 other people.  These people should be willing to help facilitate successful dragon raids, &amp; assist raid leaders with the problems of leading these raids.  If possible, these moderators should have a character L50-52 that they can keep at that level, as to actively  help dragon raids.<br>
<br>
The L47-52 population is always changing, and it's a special one.  Most of the people entering this population are inexperienced with raiding.  Many of them don't have the gear or experience they need.  The goal of the system is to assist these people in experiencing a unique experience in Everquest, and learning in the process.  Very few guilds have a core of stable 47-52 players they can count on to form the base for a solid dragon raid.  Any guild that does, likely won't 3 months down the line.<br>
<br>
These dragons require a unique solution that fits the situation, while still preserving the spirit of our server.  If the community is willing, I will work with a few other volunteers in making this happen. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uquemnwyndrunner.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Quemn Wyndrunner</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Assist Dammit!</span><br>  Posts: 744<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/23/01 9:26:20 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What does the future hold: Nagafen/Vox</span><hr size=1> well i know that Evoluxa is a guild that has no problem with people 45-52, thats where our main area is. we've got like 3-4 clerics around that level. but i see a lot of guilds passing 52 before their turn comes up like you say. i think a forum would be a good idea, and i'll join in helpin out with it with you Adun, if you like. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uphazy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Phazy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 39<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/23/01 9:35:48 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What does the future hold: Nagafen/Vox</span><hr size=1> Adune<br>
