I'm actually looking forward to reserving FG raids for our guild members who are just getting into their 40's and assisting them in learning what raids are like. That's what my friends did for me and I learned ALOT.<br>
<br>
<br>
/sigh<br>
<br>
We just had a helluva time with server outtages and such, but Naggy died despite Verants servers... We included all sorts of people from all sorts of guilds, claimed nothing but pride of accomplishment. <br>
<br>
I don't think the whole dragon reservation system was too bad, and I'm just not sure what a FCFS would be like. It's all very weird. Are we going to become a server of large guilds to compete with each other? <br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uthunderbladeone.showPublicProfile?language=EN>thunderblade one</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif height=15,width=35 BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/23/01 12:02:51 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://spiritpack.com/images/drag2.jpg height=120,width=120></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What does the future hold: Nagafen/Vox</span><hr size=1> As one of those that is holding at mid 51 waiting on a Dragon raid invite. And not being in a guild  with the resources and and being consistly passed over on invite lists form other guilds, I whole heartedly support your ideas Adun. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uadunofbrell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Adun of Brell</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Burn the Witch! [Mod]</span><br>  Posts: 1776<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/23/01 12:34:59 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.pangea.ca/~grinch/ladun.jpg width=67 height=150></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What does the future hold: Nagafen/Vox</span><hr size=1> No Bificus, not all guilds sign up in order to claim loot.  Your guild is perfect, right now to be killing dragons.  Unfortunately, our current reservation system prevents that.  Unless the leaders in your guild decide NOT to level, the people that are capable of leading a dragon raid will be over 52.  As well, a good portion of your guild's actively playing core will be over 52 by the time your slot comes around.<br>
<br>
Critical to us moving forward with good change here is the recognition that Vox &amp; Nag are special mobs that are like no other, due to the level cap, and a base minimum of level 45 or so.<br>
<br>
In a FCFS environment, Nag &amp; Vox would be raided by a lot of mostly pickup crews. Problems would be exclusion of people, lack of solid leadership &amp; experience, and the potential for some groups to hog the dragons.<br>
<br>
What I want to see is a free system that has the help of some moderators.  People that aren't just dictating who does what, but actively helping people to go out &amp; kill the dragons themselves.  Making sure people have the knowledge required, the equipment to be sucessful, and the appropriate tactics.  They'd also serve as parents of sorts.  Billy, you've had 3 turns now, it's time to give Jane a shot.  And James, Sarah, you both want to lead a raid.  We'd like to help you do that together.<br>
<br>
I want a person to be able to indicate their interest at L45, obtain the gear needed, join a raid as an observer at 45, then join a raid later at 47 or so as a participant.  As they level, I want them to be able to help the next set of L45's as they're 50-52.  At the end, you have a solid core of people that have successfully raided a dragon several times, perhaps even obtaining a special item.  When they come out, they have learned how to raid, how to help lead raids, and have cooperated with their fellow Brellians in a momentus task.<br>
<br>
As well, I'd like to bring in a few people that are L55+ each raid.  To help buff, help coordinate, &amp; get to know people.  I've been astounded when talking to lower level people about some of the attitudes towards the higher level guilds.  In the end, we're all human beings, and we genuinely want people to like us, and be our friends.  A positive experience with someone from say Watchers, Enshadowed, or SR as people enter their raiding levels will do wonders a few months down the road, when people have the choice to work something out, or fight it out.<br>
<br>
The attitudes formed by this sort of exercise WILL preserve the spirit of Brell in the future. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubificus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bificus</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.flspot.com/loa/mb/loa_iconsm.gif WIDTH=29 HEIGHT=17 BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 215<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/23/01 12:44:19 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What does the future hold: Nagafen/Vox</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Your guild is perfect, right now to be killing dragons. Unfortunately, our current reservation system prevents that.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> As well, a good portion of your guild's actively playing core will be over 52 by the time your slot comes around.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Actually the way it went, we have had our chance at both Naggy and Vox with our guild's active under 53 people participating under the current reservation system. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uadunofbrell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Adun of Brell</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Burn the Witch! [Mod]</span><br>  Posts: 1777<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/23/01 1:06:39 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.pangea.ca/~grinch/ladun.jpg width=67 height=150></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What does the future hold: Nagafen/Vox</span><hr size=1> Your guild reached 47+, decided to reserve dragons, and then several months later, when your turn came up, your people were still under 52?  Lucky you guys.  I'll have to go check how long the Nag/Vox rotations are.  I was under the impression a lot of people out-level their reservations.<br>
<br>
32 &amp; 30 names on Nag &amp; Vox respectively.  At an average of 7 days per kill (More due to guilds not killing as soon as he pops, less due to servers going down) that's over 7 months.<br>
<br>
Seven months ago, my monk Adune didn't even exist.  For most people out there, seven months is far too long to wait on a list for a mob that has a L52 cap. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uadunofbrell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Adun of Brell</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10> at: 4/23/01 1:16:53 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubificus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bificus</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.flspot.com/loa/mb/loa_iconsm.gif WIDTH=29 HEIGHT=17 BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 217<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/23/01 1:16:37 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What does the future hold: Nagafen/Vox</span><hr size=1> Our first joining the rotations was in December. The Guild member who signed us up was 48 at that time <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
